[[George Duke]] produced two [[Grammy Award for Best Jazz Vocal Album|Grammy Award]]-winning albums: [[In the Moment – Live in Concert]] and [[The Calling: Celebrating Sarah Vaughan]]. He also produced his own albums and various fellow musicians', including [[Deniece Williams]], [[Howard Hewett]], [[Jeffrey Osborne]], [[Al Jarreau]] and [[Rachelle Ferrell]] to name a few

[[Laylaw]] produced tracks on [[Revenue Retrievin': Overtime Shift]], [[Guilty by Affiliation]], [[Laugh Now, Cry Later]], [[Strictly 4 My N.I.G.G.A.Z...]], [[You Better Ask Somebody]], [[Ass, Gas, or Cash (No One Rides for Free)]], [[Addictive Hip Hop Muzick]], [[Livin' Like Hustlers]], [[On Anotha Level]], [[Lethal Injection (album)|Lethal Injection]], [[Vocally Pimpin']], [[The Lawhouse Experience, Volume One]], [[South Central Los Skanless]], [[R U Still Down? (Remember Me)]], etc.
Among his own studio albums, [[Roy Ayers]] produced for [[Sylvia Striplin]], [[Erykah Badu]], [[Wayne Henderson]], [[RAMP]], [[Guru (rapper)|GuRu]] and [[Groove Armada]] to name a few.

[[Stanley Clarke]] produced a [[Grammy Award for Best Contemporary Jazz Album|Grammy Award]]-winning album [[The Stanley Clarke Band]]. Beside his own albums, he also produced various fellow musicians', including [[Brenda Russell]], [[Roy Ayers]], [[SMV (band)|S.M.V.]], [[Rodney Saulsberry]] and [[Rodney Franklin]] to name a few.
